# Hair Hack — Agent Workflow

Skills: [addyosmani/agent-skills](https://github.com/addyosmani/agent-skills) via `.cursor/skills/` (run `./scripts/install-agent-skills.sh` after clone).

**Status dashboard:** `docs/STATUS.md` — read before starting work.

## Lifecycle

```
DEFINE → PLAN → BUILD → VERIFY → REVIEW → SHIP
```

| Phase | Skill | Doc |
|-------|-------|-----|
| Define | `spec-driven-development` | `docs/SPEC.md` |
| Plan | `planning-and-task-breakdown` | `docs/PLAN.md`, `docs/TASKS.md` |
| Build | `incremental-implementation` | one task ID per branch |
| UI | `frontend-ui-engineering` | |
| API | `api-and-interface-design` | |
| Tests | `test-driven-development` | |
| Browser QA | `browser-testing-with-devtools` | |
| Review | `code-review-and-quality` | before every PR |
| Legal UI | `security-and-hardening` | `docs/legal/COMPLIANCE.md` |
| Ship | `shipping-and-launch` | after Phase 1 + legal gate |

## Operating rules (non-negotiable)

1. **Task before code** — pick an ID from `docs/TASKS.md`; scope change → update `docs/SPEC.md` first.
2. **One slice** — implement → `npm run check` → commit → update `docs/STATUS.md`.
3. **Surface assumptions** — list them before non-trivial work.
4. **No secrets in git** — `.env.local` only.
5. **Legal** — consent + disclaimers per `docs/legal/COMPLIANCE.md`; no clinic pilot before counsel sign-off.

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev
npm test
npm run typecheck
npm run check          # typecheck + test + build — run before PR
./scripts/install-agent-skills.sh
```

## PR format

- Branch: `feature/T1.4.1-slider`
- Title: `T1.4.1: before/after slider`
- Body: link task, `npm run check` result, screenshots if UI

## Boundaries

- **Always:** server-side validation; prompts in `src/lib/prompts.ts`; providers via `src/lib/providers/`.
- **Ask first:** new deps, persist photos, new image provider, production deploy.
- **Never:** commit secrets; raw OpenAI errors to UI; skip tests to ship.
